The International Maritime Bureau reported 83 ship attacks off Somalia, with 33 hijacked.
The EU launched a security operation to combat piracy.
Pirates seized the Saudi tanker Sirius Star, the largest ever hijacked.
NATO considers long-term missions against piracy.
The Faina and its crew are held off Somalia.
Vela International works to release the crew.
The Saudi tanker, fully loaded with crude, is worth $100 million.
The hijacking highlights the pirates' capabilities and the difficulty of patrolling the vast Indian Ocean.
The situation underscores the need for stronger maritime security measures.
